 scientific publications, country house guides, and auction catalogs to highlight the thickening descriptions of domestic interiors. Considering the prose works of John Bunyan, Samuel Pepys, Aphra Behn, Daniel Defoe, Samuel Richardson, David Hume, Ann Radcliffe, and Sir Walter Scott, The Prose of Things is the first full account of the historic shift in the art of describing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  a18th century, 1700s, transformation, image, literature, literary, critique, criticism, analysis, close reading, analytical, theory, theoretical, english major, college, university, higher ed, educational, textbook, woolf, setting, description, figurative language, visual, landscape, novel, victorian, culture, cultural, perception, science, nature, natural, consumer, philosophical, domestic, john bunyan, aphra behn, daniel defoe, ann radcliffe, sir walter scott.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022687158540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226225029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226225029/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles